# NOTE: `_generated/` is intentionally tracked in git. Per the Convex
# CLI docs (https://docs.convex.dev/cli/reference/codegen):
#
#   "This code is generated automatically while running `npx convex
#    dev` and should be committed to the repo (your code won't
#    typecheck without it!). Regenerating it explicitly is rarely
#    needed (e.g. in CI to ensure the correct code was checked in)."
#
# Keeping the generated files in git means the build pipeline does not
# need network access to the Convex deployment and does not need any
# Convex env vars. If you change a file under `convex/`, run
# `npx convex codegen` locally and commit the resulting diff under
# `convex/_generated/`.